<div id="review_419855990" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/419855990" />
    <a title="Bibek Thapa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7193378-bibek-thapa"><img alt="Bibek Thapa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1578574685p2/7193378.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/419855990?book_show_action=true">Sep 22, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bibek Thapa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bibek Thapa" href="/user/show/7193378-bibek-thapa">Bibek Thapa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780312428167" href="/book/show/6277983-someday-this-pain-will-be-useful-to-you">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7193378-bibek-thapa?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7193378-bibek-thapa?shelf=books-2-movies">books-2-movies</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7193378-bibek-thapa?shelf=inspirational">inspirational</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7193378-bibek-thapa?shelf=lgbtqia">lgbtqia</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer419855990" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5059309053362076629"><b>Be patient and tough; someday this pain will be useful to you. <br/> – Ovid </b><br/><br/>I picked up this book because of its title. While a mouthful, the title of the book was interesting, along with the cover, so I thought I’d give it a try. And good thing I did.<br/>The story is about eighteen years of James Sveck, who instead of planning for his freshmen year at Brown is looking at real estate options in Midwest. James doesn’t like people in general; he hates it when people talk just for the sake of talking. All h</span>
  <span id="freeText5059309053362076629" style="display:none"><b>Be patient and tough; someday this pain will be useful to you. <br /> – Ovid </b><br /><br />I picked up this book because of its title. While a mouthful, the title of the book was interesting, along with the cover, so I thought I’d give it a try. And good thing I did.<br />The story is about eighteen years of James Sveck, who instead of planning for his freshmen year at Brown is looking at real estate options in Midwest. James doesn’t like people in general; he hates it when people talk just for the sake of talking. All he wants to do is buy a house, get a common job and read all the books that he couldn’t read due to school and whatnot. In all sense, James is a loner. But a very interesting loner at that.<br /> Someday This Pain Will Be Useful to You is a beautiful story of self-discovery and finding answers. I really liked James quirky attitude and the dialogues. I loved the writing and the slow, yet captivating, pace of the novel. This is one of those stories where you don’t find a strong plot but is still unputdownable.<br />I loved James after only a few pages in. His view of life and his comments were interesting and refreshing. I could relate to him and his point of view in so many places, which I guess made this book all the more appealing for me. The only problem that I had with the story was that James’ gloomy view of life was sometimes a little too gloomy for my taste. Also, James acted really stupidly in some places and his explanation for doing what his did made zero sense to me. The ending of the book feels sort of incomplete, so be sure to keep it in mind before you dive into the book. Other than these few problems, Someday This Pain Will Be Useful to You is a marvelous book that I will definitely recommend to anyone who enjoys reading about life and its complications, and loves to find a deeper meaning in things.<br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5059309053362076629" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


