<div id="review_555123222" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/555123222" />
    <a title="Richard Kramer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8281392-richard-kramer"><img alt="Richard Kramer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442624410p2/8281392.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/555123222?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Richard Kramer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Richard Kramer" href="/user/show/8281392-richard-kramer">Richard Kramer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer555123222" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13969907870851478458">This book was recommended to me AFTER my own book about a gay teen (who&apos;s not the main character!) was finished and published. Knowing how hard it is to do that well I think Cameron does it VERY well, indeed. I&apos;m about to read his CORAL GLYNN, and I&apos;m looking forward to it. I withhold a fifth star as I felt the book doesn&apos;t quite make it to home plate, or base, or whatever the straight boys say. For me, it&apos;s halfway between third and home, and that&apos;s a very admirable place to be. That said -- wo</span>
  <span id="freeText13969907870851478458" style="display:none">This book was recommended to me AFTER my own book about a gay teen (who's not the main character!) was finished and published. Knowing how hard it is to do that well I think Cameron does it VERY well, indeed. I'm about to read his CORAL GLYNN, and I'm looking forward to it. I withhold a fifth star as I felt the book doesn't quite make it to home plate, or base, or whatever the straight boys say. For me, it's halfway between third and home, and that's a very admirable place to be. That said -- would I give my own book five stars? On some days, yes. On others, no. As Mr Sondheim says: Art isn't easy. But, then again, neither are artists.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13969907870851478458" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


