      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alexander" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alexander" href="/user/show/145922-alexander">Alexander</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer8382106" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16930540337827602608">I read this novel in two days. It&apos;s a kind of queer Catcher In The Rye, and it&apos;s about a young man who&apos;s willing to take on the cost of being himself before everyone else is willing to let him, in one way---even as he is also not at all ready to own up to who he really is, not just yet. Cameron&apos;s writing and structure are impeccable, as always.</span>
  <span id="freeText16930540337827602608" style="display:none">I read this novel in two days. It's a kind of queer Catcher In The Rye, and it's about a young man who's willing to take on the cost of being himself before everyone else is willing to let him, in one way---even as he is also not at all ready to own up to who he really is, not just yet. Cameron's writing and structure are impeccable, as always.</span>
